whenever I see her.

00:16.099 --> 00:20.437
That kind of thing is important to girls,
but looking nice is hard.

00:22.439 --> 00:23.982
Yeah. Look at you.

00:24.065 --> 00:25.442
Cock of the walk.

00:26.776 --> 00:28.445
You know, because of your hair.

00:29.446 --> 00:30.613
That makes no sense.

00:31.281 --> 00:34.367
I look nothing like a rooster.
Roosters don't even have hair.

00:34.451 --> 00:36.453
They have a coxcomb, which is fleshy.

00:36.536 --> 00:38.788
Whoa, whoa, that's like what, the...

00:38.872 --> 00:40.874
what, the red thing on a chicken's head?

00:40.957 --> 00:42.250
Yes.

00:43.209 --> 00:44.461
Coxcomb.

00:45.628 --> 00:47.172
That's a funny word.

00:53.970 --> 00:57.098
[Sam]  As far as birds go,
chickens aren't as cool as penguins,

00:57.182 --> 00:59.434
but they have some interesting habits.

01:01.352 --> 01:04.773
In a natural setting,
a rooster will entice hens into mating

01:04.856 --> 01:07.609
by spreading his feathers
and performing a demonstrative dance.

01:08.985 --> 01:10.028
Jeez!

01:10.904 --> 01:13.823
-Don't sneak up. You made me overzest.
-Why so jumpy?

01:13.907 --> 01:15.533
I know. I couldn't help myself.

01:15.617 --> 01:18.578
-These lemon squares look delicious.
-They're not for you.

01:18.661 --> 01:20.580
-They're for group.
-All right, okay.

01:20.663 --> 01:22.499
Okay, they look fantastic.

01:36.888 --> 01:38.515
[Sam]  You may see him dip one wing

01:38.598 --> 01:41.226
and dance around the female
in a circular pattern.

01:44.312 --> 01:46.022
Shit, Casey.

01:46.105 --> 01:48.149
That's a grown-ass man right there.

01:48.233 --> 01:50.652
Are you banging,
or are you still in handy land?

01:50.735 --> 01:53.071
[scoffs] Yeah, right.
Casey's a total prude.

01:53.154 --> 01:55.281
-She's never even kissed a boy.
-[laughing]

01:55.365 --> 01:59.119
You didn't mention a boyfriend. How could
you not tell me you have a boyfriend?

01:59.202 --> 02:00.745
We're just hanging out.

02:00.829 --> 02:02.831
-Mm-hmm.
-Hanging out with his dick.

02:02.914 --> 02:04.541
[laughing]

02:07.544 --> 02:08.545
Are you?

02:10.338 --> 02:14.175
-[whispering] Hanging out with his dick.
-[laughing] No. Sharice.

02:14.259 --> 02:15.510
Go away.

02:16.469 --> 02:18.680
[Sam]  But enticing human girls
into mating

02:18.763 --> 02:22.267
or just being your girlfriend
takes different skills.

02:22.350 --> 02:23.726
It requires research.

02:23.810 --> 02:26.521
You can't just ask a girl out.

02:26.604 --> 02:28.940
You have to learn the important things
about her first.

02:29.023 --> 02:30.567
What's your favorite type of lemonade?

02:31.860 --> 02:33.820
Uh, regular?

02:35.446 --> 02:36.698
Do you like movies?

02:37.448 --> 02:39.784
Yes. I love them.

02:39.868 --> 02:41.870
Do you have any fears or phobias?

02:43.246 --> 02:45.623
-Nope.
-What are your favorite winter sports?

02:47.584 --> 02:50.086
Well, we have been
snowshoeing a couple times.

02:52.046 --> 02:54.591
"We"? As in you and your mom.

02:55.216 --> 02:56.259
Me and my boyfriend.

02:56.885 --> 02:58.177
Snowshoeing was his idea.

02:58.261 --> 02:59.762
I hate the cold. [chuckles]

03:01.306 --> 03:02.390
You have a boyfriend?

03:02.473 --> 03:04.183
Mm-hmm. Miles.

03:05.560 --> 03:08.897
Anyway, it's great that
you're showing so much interest in others.

03:08.980 --> 03:10.523
We've been working on that.

03:10.607 --> 03:12.734
[fading] But how about we get back
to you?

03:12.817 --> 03:15.612
Now, when Mr. Tavern's
voice bothers you...

03:28.499 --> 03:31.544
[Sam]  When I was younger,
if I got upset or stressed,

03:31.628 --> 03:35.215
I would hit or bang my head or yell.

03:35.298 --> 03:38.176
Now I try to use replacement
behaviors instead.

03:44.474 --> 03:45.391
Sam.

03:46.100 --> 03:47.143
Is everything okay?

03:49.187 --> 03:50.396
Want to talk?

03:51.856 --> 03:53.233
Maybe I should talk to Mom.

03:53.316 --> 03:56.486
That's usually how things go around here,
but Mom has her group tonight.

03:56.569 --> 03:58.238
Okay? Maybe I can help.

04:01.741 --> 04:02.659
I like a girl.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.119
Really?

04:07.372 --> 04:09.916
That's good. What's she like?

04:09.999 --> 04:12.418
She's smart, and she's pretty.

04:12.502 --> 04:15.046
And she has a boyfriend-- Miles.

04:15.129 --> 04:16.256
Stupid Miles!

04:17.131 --> 04:18.633
[Doug] Well, that sucks.

04:18.716 --> 04:21.135
But, you know,
it's not the end of the world.

04:21.678 --> 04:23.680
Mom had a boyfriend when I first met her.

04:27.016 --> 04:30.311
-She did?
-This guy Gerald Redenbach.

04:30.395 --> 04:32.855
