05:10.393 --> 05:14.355
I should make myself available
in case Miles goes away or dies.

05:15.023 --> 05:17.692
Or they break up amicably.

05:20.862 --> 05:22.822
Okay. I'll do that.

05:22.905 --> 05:24.032
You should.

05:29.078 --> 05:30.705
I think this went well.

05:30.788 --> 05:31.956
Me, too.

05:32.790 --> 05:34.042
[chuckles]

05:36.544 --> 05:38.504
I know we're always, um...

05:38.588 --> 05:40.590
talking in here about, you know,

05:40.673 --> 05:43.217
taking time for ourselves

05:43.301 --> 05:44.343
and I did.

05:45.845 --> 05:48.014
I took a dance class. Silly.

05:48.514 --> 05:49.682
Um...

05:49.766 --> 05:52.185
The teacher thought I was really good.

05:52.977 --> 05:54.937
Really silly. But she did say that.

05:55.021 --> 05:57.690
And this is nuts, but afterwards,

05:57.774 --> 06:01.569
we all went to a bar, and I met a guy.

06:01.652 --> 06:05.364
I mean, not a guy-guy.
I'm married. You all know Doug.

06:05.448 --> 06:08.493
Not really, he doesn't come to these,
they're not his "thing."

06:08.576 --> 06:09.869
Whose thing are they?

06:09.952 --> 06:12.622
[laughs] It's not like we come here
for the fun of it.

06:12.705 --> 06:13.748
No offense.

06:13.831 --> 06:15.041
I like you guys.

06:15.124 --> 06:16.834
Marjorie, you.

06:16.918 --> 06:21.130
Um, so, Sam. Anyway. Um...

06:21.214 --> 06:23.633
Sam is-- he had a good week, you know?

06:23.716 --> 06:26.135
But the thing is, at this bar,

06:27.053 --> 06:32.350
for the first time since,
probably, Sam was diagnosed,

06:33.017 --> 06:36.521
